My favorite project was the css colors borders and shadows.
It was so much fun getting to see my code come to life . 
Heres a bit of my code / Notes.



** Borders **
border-width: Defines the width of the border (e.g., 5px).
border-color: Sets the color of the border (e.g., blue).
border-style: Determines the style of the border (e.g., solid, dotted).
border-radius: Rounds the edges of the border (e.g., 5px).

/* Border for the first box */
.box1 {
  border: 5px solid blue;
}

/* Border for the second box */
.box2 {
  border: 2px dotted red;
  border-radius: 5px;
}



** Colors **
color: Sets the color of the text. 
Can use hexadecimal (e.g., #FFC300) or RGB (e.g., rgb(235, 62, 71)).
background-color: Sets the background color of an element.

/* Color for the first text */
.text1 {
  color: #FFC300;
}

/* Color for the second text */
.text2 {
  color: rgb(235, 62, 71);
}

/* Background color for boxes */
.box {
  background-color: #f0f0f0; /* Adjust the color as needed */
}




** Opacity **
Background-color: Use rgba to set color and opacity (e.g., rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.6)).
Text Opacity: Sets the opacity level of an element (e.g., 0.5).

/* Background color with opacity for Box 3 */
.box3 {
  background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.6); /* Adjust the color as needed */
}

/* Opacity for all h2 elements */
h2 {
  opacity: 0.5;
}




** Box Shadows **
box-shadow: Adds shadow to elements. 
Properties include horizontal offset, vertical offset, blur-radius, and color.

/* Shadow for Box 5 */
.box5 {
  box-shadow: 8px 20px 15px teal;
}

/* Shadow for Box 6 */
.box6 {
  box-shadow: 5px -10px 0 #800000;
}



